  "rich_text": [
    "Smart parking",
    "The IGP smart parking system makes use of advanced computer vision technology in order to identify vacant parking or occupied parking and then correspondingly turns on an appropriate green/red/blue signal of vacant or occupied parking.\n​\nThe system includes the option of up to 2 cameras which enable the identification of up to 3 parking lots in one unit.\n​\nMarking free/occupied parking spaces using red/green/blue LED lights.\nExtremely reliable technology for identifying the condition of the parking space using a camera (not ultrasonic)\nIdentification of car numbers.\nFinding the location of a car in the parking lot.\nSafety - very low voltage feed.\nCommunication Rs485, TCP/IP\nMonitoring of 2 parking spaces per unit.\nOptions:\nSignage and guidance system based on 32' screens\nAn alarm report for maintenance purposes that includes the possibility of communication alarms and unit faults.\nProduction of a monthly report with a daily breakdown regarding the amount of uses in the parking lots in the building.\nProduction of a daily graph that includes a parking lot usage profile by time of day\nDisplaying data in real time on AutoCAD images of the parking lot.",
    "Related Products",
    "Control Applications Ltd",
    "making contact\nPhone: +972-3-6474998\n​\nFax: +972-3-6474598\nEmail:\ncal@ddc.co.il",
    "opening hours\nControl Applications Ltd\nSunday - Thursday\n08:00 - 17:00",
    "Address\n25 Barzel Street, Tel Aviv\n6971035\nIsrael",
    "© Copyright - Control Applications Ltd"
  ],
